# Audit / rotation working docs — do not commit
AUDIT.md
ROTATION.md

# Belt-and-suspenders for stray tsc emits inside convex sources. Gap 2 Phase 1
# moved convex/ into packages/crm-api/, so the patterns now live there. Phase 2
# will enable emit (to dist/), so these patterns guard against accidental emit
# *into* the convex source tree (which would confuse `npx convex dev`'s
# esbuild entry-point scan with two outputs sharing the same path).
packages/crm-api/convex/**/*.js
packages/crm-api/convex/**/*.d.ts
packages/crm-api/convex/**/*.d.ts.map
!packages/crm-api/convex/convex.config.ts
!packages/crm-api/convex/_generated/

# Root-level guard: the canonical convex/ tree lives in packages/crm-api/.
# Documented Convex CLI behavior: `npx convex codegen` invoked from a
# directory without a convex/ tree will bootstrap an empty one (with
# `ApiFromModules<{}>` for api.d.ts). Easy to trigger by accident in a
# long shell session if cwd drifts from packages/crm-api/ back to the
# repo root between commands. Ignoring the path keeps any accidental
# stub out of the working tree silently. The fix is "always cd into
# packages/crm-api/ before running npx convex anything" — see also
# CLAUDE.md's schema-ownership note. Investigation trail:
# `~/Documents/quilt/02_reference/projects/photographer_crm/
# gap-2-phase-1-followups.md` Finding 2.
/convex/
